#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.90"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.90:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.90:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga"
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.90:0.3"
msgid "90. Channasutta"
msgstr "90. With Channa"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.90:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ sambahulā therā bhikkhū bārāṇasiyaṃ viharanti isipatane "
"migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time several senior mendicants were staying near Benares, in the deer "
"park at Isipatana."

#. VAR: avāpuraṇaṃ → apāpuraṇaṃ (si, s1-3, km) | avāpuranaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.90:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā channo sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito avāpuraṇaṃ ādāya "
"vihārena vihāraṃ upasaṅkamitvā there bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Channa came out of retreat. Taking a "
"key, he went from dwelling to dwelling, going up to the senior mendicants "
"and saying:"

msgctxt "sn22.90:1.3"
msgid ""
"“ovadantu maṃ āyasmanto therā, anusāsantu maṃ āyasmanto therā, karontu me "
"āyasmanto therā dhammiṃ kathaṃ, yathāhaṃ dhammaṃ passeyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“May the venerable senior mendicants advise me and instruct me! May they "
"give me a Dhamma talk so that I can see the teaching!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.90:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, therā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ channaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "When he said this, the senior mendicants said to Venerable Channa:"

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.2"
msgid "“rūpaṃ kho, āvuso channa, aniccaṃ;"
msgstr "“Reverend Channa, form,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.3"
msgid "vedanā aniccā;"
msgstr "feeling,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.4"
msgid "saññā aniccā;"
msgstr "perception,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.5"
msgid "saṅkhārā aniccā;"
msgstr "choices,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.6"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ."
msgstr "and consciousness are impermanent."

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.7"
msgid "Rūpaṃ anattā;"
msgstr "Form,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.8"
msgid "vedanā …"
msgstr "feeling,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.9"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.10"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.11"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ anattā."
msgstr "and consciousness are not-self."

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.12"
msgid "Sabbe saṅkhārā aniccā;"
msgstr "All conditions are impermanent."

msgctxt "sn22.90:2.13"
msgid "sabbe dhammā anattā”ti."
msgstr "All things are not-self.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.133"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.90:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato channassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Channa thought:"

#. VAR: mayhampi kho etaṃ evaṃ → mayhaṃpi kho evaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn22.90:3.2"
msgid "“mayhampi kho etaṃ evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“I too think in this way. …"

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.3"
msgid "‘rūpaṃ aniccaṃ, vedanā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.4"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.5"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.6"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.7"
msgid "rūpaṃ anattā, vedanā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.8"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.9"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.10"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ anattā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.11"
msgid "Sabbe saṅkhārā aniccā, sabbe dhammā anattā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.12"
msgid ""
"Atha ca pana me sabbasaṅkhārasamathe sabbūpadhipaṭinissagge taṇhākkhaye "
"virāge nirodhe nibbāne cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati "
"nādhimuccati."
msgstr ""
"And yet my mind isn’t eager, confident, settled, and decided about the "
"stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of "
"craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment."

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.13"
msgid "Paritassanā upādānaṃ uppajjati;"
msgstr "Anxiety and grasping arise."

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.14"
msgid "paccudāvattati mānasaṃ:"
msgstr "And the mind reverts to thinking:"

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.15"
msgid "‘atha ko carahi me attā’ti?"
msgstr "‘So then who exactly is my self?’"

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.16"
msgid "Na kho panevaṃ dhammaṃ passato hoti."
msgstr "But that doesn’t happen for someone who sees the teaching."

msgctxt "sn22.90:3.17"
msgid "Ko nu kho me tathā dhammaṃ deseyya yathāhaṃ dhammaṃ passeyyan”ti."
msgstr "Who can teach me the Dhamma so that I can see the teaching?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.90:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato channassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Channa thought:"

msgctxt "sn22.90:4.2"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme satthu ceva "
"saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ, pahoti ca me āyasmā "
"ānando tathā dhammaṃ desetuṃ yathāhaṃ dhammaṃ passeyyaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“The Venerable Ānanda is staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery. He’s "
"praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions. He’"
"s quite capable of teaching me the Dhamma so that I can see the teaching."

#. VAR: vissaṭṭhi → visaṭṭhi (pts1) | vissatthi (?)
msgctxt "sn22.90:4.3"
msgid "atthi ca me āyasmante ānande tāvatikā vissaṭṭhi."
msgstr "Since I have so much trust in Venerable Ānanda,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:4.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti."
msgstr "why don’t I go to see him?”"

msgctxt "sn22.90:4.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā channo senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena kosambī "
"ghositārāmo yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena "
"saddhiṃ sammodi … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā channo āyasmantaṃ "
"ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Channa set his lodgings in order and, taking his bowl and robe, set out "
"for Kosambi. He went to see Ānanda in Ghosita’s Monastery, exchanged "
"greetings with him, and told him what had happened. Then he said:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.90:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Ekamidāhaṃ, āvuso ānanda, samayaṃ bārāṇasiyaṃ viharāmi isipatane migadāye."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.2"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ, āvuso, sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito avāpuraṇaṃ ādāya "
"vihārena vihāraṃ upasaṅkamiṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā there bhikkhū etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.4"
msgid ""
"‘ovadantu maṃ āyasmanto therā, anusāsantu maṃ āyasmanto therā, karontu me "
"āyasmanto therā dhammiṃ kathaṃ yathāhaṃ dhammaṃ passeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, maṃ, āvuso, therā bhikkhū etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.6"
msgid "‘rūpaṃ kho, āvuso channa, aniccaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.7"
msgid "vedanā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.8"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.9"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.10"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.11"
msgid "rūpaṃ anattā … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ anattā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:5.13"
msgid "Sabbe saṅkhārā aniccā, sabbe dhammā anattā’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.134"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.90:6.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.2"
msgid "‘mayhampi kho etaṃ evaṃ hoti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.3"
msgid "rūpaṃ aniccaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.4"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ, rūpaṃ anattā, vedanā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.5"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.6"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.7"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ anattā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.8"
msgid "Sabbe saṅkhārā aniccā, sabbe dhammā anattā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.9"
msgid ""
"Atha ca pana me sabbasaṅkhārasamathe sabbūpadhipaṭinissagge taṇhākkhaye "
"virāge nirodhe nibbāne cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati "
"nādhimuccati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.10"
msgid "Paritassanā upādānaṃ uppajjati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.11"
msgid "paccudāvattati mānasaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.12"
msgid "‘atha ko carahi me attā’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.13"
msgid "Na kho panevaṃ dhammaṃ passato hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:6.14"
msgid "Ko nu kho me tathā dhammaṃ deseyya yathāhaṃ dhammaṃ passeyyanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.90:7.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme satthu ceva "
"saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ, pahoti ca me āyasmā "
"ānando tathā dhammaṃ desetuṃ yathāhaṃ dhammaṃ passeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:7.3"
msgid "Atthi ca me āyasmante ānande tāvatikā vissaṭṭhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:7.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:7.5"
msgid "Ovadatu maṃ, āyasmā ānando;"
msgstr ""
"“May Venerable Ānanda advise me and instruct me! May he give me a Dhamma "
"talk so that I can see the teaching!”"

msgctxt "sn22.90:7.6"
msgid "anusāsatu maṃ, āyasmā ānando;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.90:7.7"
msgid "karotu me, āyasmā ānando dhammiṃ kathaṃ yathāhaṃ dhammaṃ passeyyan”ti."
msgstr ""

# Reading khila rather than khīla. I think this passage has a specific Vinaya meaning: he has confessed and healed the breach in the sangha. It’s difficult to convey that sense.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
#. VAR: taṃ → taṃ (bj, s1-3, km)
#. VAR: chindi → pabhindi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.90:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Ettakenapi mayaṃ āyasmato channassa attamanā api nāma taṃ āyasmā channo āvi "
"akāsi khīlaṃ chindi."
msgstr ""
"“I’m already delighted with Venerable Channa. Hopefully you’ve opened "
"yourself up and cut through your emotional barrenness."

msgctxt "sn22.90:8.2"
msgid "Odahāvuso channa, sotaṃ;"
msgstr "Listen well, Channa."

#. VAR: bhabbosi → bhabbo tvaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn22.90:8.3"
msgid "bhabbosi dhammaṃ viññātun”ti."
msgstr "You are capable of understanding the teaching.”"

#. VAR: tāvatakeneva → tāvadeva (si)
msgctxt "sn22.90:8.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato channassa tāvatakeneva uḷāraṃ pītipāmojjaṃ uppajji:"
msgstr "Then right away Channa was filled with lofty rapture and joy:"

msgctxt "sn22.90:8.5"
msgid "“bhabbo kirasmi dhammaṃ viññātun”ti."
msgstr "“It seems I’m capable of understanding the teaching!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.135"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.90:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso channa, bhagavato sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ "
"kaccānagottaṃ bhikkhuṃ ovadantassa—"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Channa, I heard and learned in the presence of the Buddha his "
"advice to the mendicant Kaccānagotta:"

# MS omits quote marks. Don’t forget to adjust the nesting level.
msgctxt "sn22.90:9.2"
msgid ""
"dvayanissito khvāyaṃ, kaccāna, loko yebhuyyena atthitañceva natthitañca."
msgstr ""
"‘Kaccāna, this world mostly relies on the dual notions of existence and non-"
"existence."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.3"
msgid ""
"Lokasamudayaṃ kho, kaccāna, yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passato yā loke "
"natthitā, sā na hoti."
msgstr ""
"But when you truly see the origin of the world with right understanding, you "
"won’t have the notion of non-existence regarding the world."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.4"
msgid ""
"Lokanirodhaṃ kho, kaccāna, yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passato yā loke "
"atthitā, sā na hoti."
msgstr ""
"And when you truly see the cessation of the world with right understanding, "
"you won’t have the notion of existence regarding the world."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.5"
msgid "Upayupādānābhinivesavinibandho khvāyaṃ, kaccāna, loko yebhuyyena "
msgstr ""
"The world is for the most part shackled to attraction, grasping, and "
"insisting. "

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.6"
msgid ""
"taṃ cāyaṃ upayupādānaṃ cetaso adhiṭṭhānābhinivesānusayaṃ na upeti na "
"upādiyati nādhiṭṭhāti ‘attā me’ti."
msgstr ""
"But if—when it comes to this attraction, grasping, mental dedication, "
"insistence, and underlying tendency—you don’t get atracted, grasp, and "
"commit to the notion “my self”,"

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.7"
msgid ""
"Dukkhameva uppajjamānaṃ uppajjati, dukkhaṃ nirujjhamānaṃ nirujjhatīti na "
"kaṅkhati na vicikicchati."
msgstr ""
"you’ll have no doubt or uncertainty that what arises is just suffering "
"arising, and what ceases is just suffering ceasing."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.8"
msgid "Aparappaccayā ñāṇamevassa ettha hoti."
msgstr "Your knowledge about this is independent of others."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.9"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, kaccāna, sammādiṭṭhi hoti."
msgstr "This is how right view is defined."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.10"
msgid "Sabbamatthīti kho, kaccāna, ayameko anto."
msgstr "“All exists”: this is one extreme."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.11"
msgid "Sabbaṃ natthīti ayaṃ dutiyo anto."
msgstr "“All doesn’t exist”: this is the second extreme."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.12"
msgid ""
"Ete te, kaccāna, ubho ante anupagamma majjhena tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti—"
msgstr ""
"Avoiding these two extremes, the Realized One teaches by the middle way:"

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.13"
msgid "avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārā;"
msgstr "“Ignorance is a condition for choices."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.14"
msgid "saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Choices are a condition for consciousness. …"

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.15"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.16"
msgid "Avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā saṅkhāranirodho … pe …"
msgstr ""
"When ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, choices cease. …"

msgctxt "sn22.90:9.17"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.”’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.90:10.1"
msgid ""
"“Evametaṃ, āvuso ānanda, hoti yesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ tādisā sabrahmacārayo "
"anukampakā atthakāmā ovādakā anusāsakā."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Ānanda, this is how it is when you have such venerables as "
"spiritual companions to advise and instruct you out of kindness and "
"compassion."

msgctxt "sn22.90:10.2"
msgid ""
"Idañca pana me āyasmato ānandassa dhammadesanaṃ sutvā dhammo abhisamito”ti."
msgstr ""
"And now that I’ve heard this teaching from Venerable Ānanda, I’ve "
"comprehended the teaching.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.90:10.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
